BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f8297962b251277d@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T173000Z
DTEND:20260613T183000Z
SUMMARY:25 Years Of Eskimo Recordings (Nadiem Shah)
LOCATION:The Floor
DESCRIPTION:Nadiem Shah playing an infectious selection of the influential 
 label from Ghent\n\nThe promised landers have their DFA label. The low lan
 ders have Eskimo Recordings.\nThis highly influential label from Belgium i
 s as much known for its artists (Aeroplane\, Prins Thomas\, Aili) as it is
  for its compilations. It all started with the eclectic parties that took 
 place during the late nineties in the Eskimo Fabriek in Ghent. These under
 ground parties got famous for mixing new wave\, acid\, funk and rock ‘n
 ’ roll\, introducing local DJs such as The Glimmers and The Flying Dewae
 le Brothers. At The Floor label manager Nadiem Shah will takes us through 
 25 years of leftfield clubbing. Cooler than being cool. Eskimo!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
